Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.71,0:00:09.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,World War III.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.60,0:00:12.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By 2036,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.97,0:00:16.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it will have resulted in 5.7 billion casualties worldwide.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.41,0:00:17.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And this is what starts it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.44,0:00:20.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.55,0:00:22.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's only a model.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.15,0:00:23.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it transforms or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.85,0:00:25.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A time machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.09,0:00:27.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.65,0:00:31.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew you'd recognize it, Uncle.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.09,0:00:32.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then that makes this easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.35,0:00:35.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.61,0:00:41.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I refuse...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.09,0:00:43.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okarin?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.77,0:00:46.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've come here from the alpha world line.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.27,0:00:48.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Over the past three weeks,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.88,0:00:51.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I changed that world line again and again,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.35,0:00:55.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,sacrificing Kurisu to return here, \Nto the beta world line.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.60,0:01:00.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't let all of that count for nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.77,0:01:03.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kurisu-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.72,0:01:05.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kurisu?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.51,0:01:08.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wasn't that the name of the scientist
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.92,0:01:11.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who was stabbed at the Radio Building?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.42,0:01:15.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okabe Rintarou,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.44,0:01:20.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,what if I told you that the way \Nto avoid World War III
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.65,0:01:23.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is to prevent Makise Kurisu's death
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.77,0:01:27.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,on July 28th, 2010?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.85,0:01:31.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.02,0:01:33.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know the details.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.34,0:01:36.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I have one mission...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.52,0:01:38.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To save Makise Kurisu,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.54,0:01:42.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and to go to the one world line unaffected \Nby the Attractor Field:
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.29,0:01:45.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Steins Gate!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.79,0:03:20.77,Title1,,0000,0000,0000,,Open the Steins Gate
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.07,0:03:24.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Steins Gate?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.34,0:03:26.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The architects of this plan were
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.55,0:03:29.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,my father and your future self.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.28,0:03:32.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,None of it is anything more than a hypothesis.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.89,0:03:36.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's possible the theory is wrong,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.32,0:03:40.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and there is no Steins Gate world line.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.43,0:03:43.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm going anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.31,0:03:47.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll bet on the chance that \Na bright future's waiting for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.10,0:03:51.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're coming with me,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.40,0:03:52.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,then take my hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.06,0:04:02.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.68,0:04:06.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayushii didn't really understand any of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.96,0:04:09.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But if this person,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.50,0:04:14.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,this Kurisu-san, is important to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.63,0:04:17.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,shouldn't you try to help them?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.60,0:04:22.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,World War III sounds too much \Nlike one of your fantasies.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.85,0:04:25.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No one else could handle it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.47,0:04:31.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care about 5.7 billion people in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.41,0:04:33.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.30,0:04:38.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.06,0:04:41.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Board now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.49,0:04:43.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Two people can get in it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.09,0:04:44.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.52,0:04:48.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is my father's masterpiece.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.16,0:04:53.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okarin!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.58,0:04:57.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave your phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.52,0:05:01.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It might get crossed with your \Nphone in the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.94,0:05:04.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll return.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.04,0:05:09.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.85,0:05:12.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a time machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.22,0:05:12.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.98,0:05:16.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I stopped in 1975 and 2000.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.72,0:05:18.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's working fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.48,0:05:22.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's running out of fuel...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.22,0:05:24.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait, it can go from past to future?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.75,0:05:27.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course it can.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.26,0:05:28.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a time machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.81,0:05:30.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.64,0:05:33.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Is that because we're in a different world line now?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.27,0:05:34.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sit down.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.21,0:05:39.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll head to just before noon, on July 28th.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.10,0:05:40.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't change location,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.91,0:05:43.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so if we arrive too early, it'll spread \Npanic at the Radio Building,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.85,0:05:46.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,possibly affecting Makise Kurisu's actions.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.68,0:05:49.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your first time, the Gs are pretty tough.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.50,0:05:51.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.48,0:06:03.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okarin...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.20,0:06:08.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.50,0:06:10.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These always show up.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.09,0:06:11.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I guess they're like fragments of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.86,0:06:13.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pretty, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.85,0:06:20.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.22,0:06:22.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.07,0:06:24.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I think I'm going to throw up...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.38,0:06:26.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're a wimp...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.50,0:06:27.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.71,0:06:34.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let your other self encounter you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.64,0:06:37.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll cause a serious time paradox.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.26,0:06:39.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How long until her stabbing?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.68,0:06:42.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Twenty minutes or so, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.78,0:06:45.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll ready the time machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.54,0:06:47.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You protect her, Uncle.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.67,0:06:48.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop calling me that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.60,0:06:52.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}July 28th.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.66,0:06:55.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The day I saw Kurisu lying in a pool of blood,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.66,0:06:57.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'd come with Mayuri to see
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.54,0:06:59.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Professor Nakabachi's press conference.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.72,0:07:01.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I heard a noise on the roof.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.35,0:07:18.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That's right. After this, Mayuri goes \Nto the 7th-floor Upa machines.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.38,0:07:19.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Oh, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.82,0:07:22.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You called me here for this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.06,0:07:26.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There aren't many left of this series, \Nand Mayushii's...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.64,0:07:28.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Oh well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.18,0:07:30.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll take the back stairs to the 8th floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.53,0:07:34.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a metal... A metal Upa!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.56,0:07:35.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it rare?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.82,0:07:37.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.56,0:07:39.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If I make it here... {D: TC - unclear what this is supposed to mean}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.33,0:07:44.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.93,0:07:47.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,K-Kurisu?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.48,0:07:49.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-How do you know my name?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.68,0:07:53.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Kurisu is alive...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.14,0:07:55.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have we met somewhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.46,0:07:57.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kurisu...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.52,0:07:58.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you listening...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.42,0:08:03.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.35,0:08:05.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Answer me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.13,0:08:12.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I... You... {D: TC - can't hear the first word clearly. Sounds like an ore wa}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.36,0:08:21.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.31,0:08:22.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.36,0:08:31.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the handouts, you can read about \Nthe time machine's basic design.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.53,0:08:35.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will use this conference as an opportunity \Nto discuss the fundamental theory behind it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.72,0:08:36.93,Sign23A,,0000,0000,0000,,Professor Nakabachi
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.47,0:08:42.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The operation notes said that \Nyou'd be able to identify Makise Kurisu.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.17,0:08:43.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.27,0:08:44.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.29,0:08:47.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also, it's dangerous to take her outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.08,0:08:51.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we can't find out who stabbed her,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.53,0:08:54.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{D: TC - missing line}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.62,0:08:56.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The same as with Mayuri?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.43,0:08:59.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.11,0:09:00.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.53,0:09:02.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know exactly what!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.17,0:09:04.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this "time machine theory" of yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.47,0:09:05.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kerr Black Holes?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.78,0:09:06.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,World lines?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.96,0:09:08.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You stole all this from John Titor!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.66,0:09:12.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Kurisu will be stabbed right here soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.16,0:09:15.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Is she really going to be here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.39,0:09:19.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Wait! Maybe she was stabbed elsewhere \Nand brought here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.79,0:09:23.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yeah... That's possible!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.66,0:09:30.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Kurisu?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.97,0:09:33.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}So, it does happen here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.27,0:09:36.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What's she reading?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.38,0:09:39.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A time machine?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.63,0:09:43.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Is that why she's the key to changing world lines?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.08,0:09:51.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.53,0:09:54.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Daddy, I wanted you to read this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.91,0:09:55.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Daddy?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.01,0:10:00.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Professor Nakabachi?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.64,0:10:03.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You contacted me for the first time in seven years.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.69,0:10:06.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You asked me to come to \Nyour press conference, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.32,0:10:07.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was my inspiration...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.85,0:10:11.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Wait, so Kurisu's dad is...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.91,0:10:13.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I thought I could use it to theorize a time machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.55,0:10:17.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to hear your theories.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.46,0:10:21.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If this is accepted, you can use it
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.02,0:10:22.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to show everyone who kicked you out of academia...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.93,0:10:25.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't kicked out!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.10,0:10:28.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I got sick of them and left.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.57,0:10:30.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.81,0:10:33.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.58,0:10:34.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.68,0:10:37.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you're okay with it,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.11,0:10:40.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought we could put both \Nour names on the paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.14,0:10:41.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because you inspired me...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.88,0:10:43.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.96,0:10:45.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.76,0:10:49.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll publish this paper under my name.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.43,0:10:50.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.47,0:10:52.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You wouldn't steal it, right, Daddy?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.97,0:10:55.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought, no matter what, you'd never do that...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.68,0:10:56.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.40,0:11:02.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How dare you call it stealing!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.68,0:11:08.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you so smart?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.03,0:11:11.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A girl shouldn't be smarter than her father!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.45,0:11:15.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it weren't for you, I'd have been smart, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.02,0:11:17.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it weren't for you...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.03,0:11:17.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.97,0:11:28.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're that kid from earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.03,0:11:30.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.37,0:11:36.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You were plotting to ruin \Nmy conference together, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.90,0:11:41.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.80,0:11:43.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.89,0:11:45.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Daddy!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.65,0:11:47.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'll protect her!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.08,0:11:54.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How dare you insult me?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.77,0:12:02.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why, you...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.80,0:12:06.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it, Daddy!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.97,0:12:08.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.14,0:12:12.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't even speak to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.28,0:12:12.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh no!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.39,0:12:19.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.81,0:12:21.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't know how I feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.70,0:12:24.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't know how I've been humiliated...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.64,0:12:26.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The hell I've been through!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.33,0:12:29.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it weren't for you...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.25,0:12:30.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.31,0:12:32.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it weren't for you...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.30,0:12:36.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.47,0:12:45.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kurisu...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.38,0:12:51.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,K-Kurisu!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.58,0:12:56.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fools.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.31,0:12:59.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the perfect end for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.29,0:13:06.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry for involving you...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.22,0:13:07.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.81,0:13:09.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because he's my dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.80,0:13:13.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted him to accept me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.27,0:13:14.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.45,0:13:15.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kurisu...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.67,0:13:20.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm scared...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.75,0:13:27.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I... I don't want to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.06,0:13:31.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.15,0:13:33.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.07,0:13:38.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kurisu...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.64,0:13:41.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kurisu!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.30,0:13:58.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're back already!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.18,0:14:02.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okarin!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.53,0:14:07.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okarin, that blood...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.58,0:14:08.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.75,0:14:10.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not his.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.64,0:14:15.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was the one who killed Kurisu...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.81,0:14:17.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was the one who killed Kurisu...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.36,0:14:20.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was the one who killed Kurisu...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.66,0:14:22.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okarin?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.56,0:14:26.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know it hurts, but you can't give up yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.79,0:14:29.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have enough fuel to go back once more...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.55,0:14:30.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.29,0:14:32.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll just be the same!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.77,0:14:37.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Attractor Field convergence will \Nkill her all over again.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.30,0:14:42.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's your phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.68,0:14:44.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A message?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.21,0:14:45.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Open it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.28,0:14:45.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.87,0:14:47.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.29,0:14:52.31,Cellphone,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn on the TV.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.22,0:14:52.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn on the TV?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.31,0:14:53.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The TV?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.95,0:15:04.68,CellphoneL,,0000,0000,0000,,Mysterious Fire in Cargo Bay \NProfessor Nakabachi Defects to Russia
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.32,0:15:01.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The plane carrying Professor Nakabachi \Nmade it to Russia,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.59,0:15:05.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,despite a mysterious cargo bay fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.04,0:15:07.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We were very fortunate.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.21,0:15:09.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If this hadn't triggered the metal detector,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.66,0:15:12.18,Sign23B,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayushii
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.86,0:15:12.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the paper would have gone up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.45,0:15:15.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's Mayushii's metal Upa! {D: TC - missing Daru line here?}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.79,0:15:19.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look. It has Mayushii's name on it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.61,0:15:20.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.90,0:15:23.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But what's it doing in Russia?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.11,0:15:25.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That paper is the start of everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.05,0:15:32.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Next comes the international, \Ntime machine arms race.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.60,0:15:37.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To rule time is to rule the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.87,0:15:40.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And that begins a world war.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.30,0:15:46.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,5.7 billion lives are at stake.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.40,0:15:50.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Save Makise Kurisu, and change this world line!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.67,0:15:51.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's impossible...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.91,0:15:54.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just like with Mayuri.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.86,0:15:58.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what I do, it'll end up the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.32,0:16:00.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kurisu will die.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.96,0:16:03.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How can you say that after only one time?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.35,0:16:04.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One time?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.01,0:16:06.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's more than that...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.91,0:16:08.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How many times...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.45,0:16:11.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How many times do you think I've failed?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.53,0:16:14.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can tell...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.35,0:16:18.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How insane this time loop is...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.69,0:16:21.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a cruel fate it has in store...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.81,0:16:25.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew this...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.43,0:16:28.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I knew this would happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.35,0:16:29.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm tired.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.52,0:16:34.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so tired...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.59,0:16:43.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not the kind of person to quit halfway.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.77,0:16:45.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mayushii knows this!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.07,0:16:49.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not the kind of person to ever give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.27,0:16:53.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even when Mayushii couldn't \Nsay goodbye to her grandmother,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.11,0:16:56.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,you never stopped going to her grave.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.81,0:16:59.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I could say goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.93,0:17:02.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I got better!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.88,0:17:06.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So don't give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.10,0:17:15.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should have received a video file on July 28th.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.51,0:17:22.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}July 28th...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.32,0:17:23.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should be able to watch it,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.92,0:17:27.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,now that you've failed once \Nto rescue Makise Kurisu.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.38,0:17:29.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.75,0:17:31.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry I lied to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.28,0:17:33.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The plan called for you to fail once.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.62,0:17:36.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that you would see this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.34,0:17:43.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.93,0:17:47.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice to meet you, myself fifteen years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.34,0:17:49.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's Okarin!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.41,0:17:54.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you've opened this message,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.38,0:17:57.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,then you've failed to rescue Kurisu.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.36,0:18:00.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It must have been painful.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.13,0:18:05.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that pain gave rise to my obsession.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.61,0:18:09.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So it had to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.31,0:18:13.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You might say it was a part of the preparation.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.14,0:18:17.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now we can begin the plan for real.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.91,0:18:19.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The plan to save Makise Kurisu,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.71,0:18:21.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and enter Steins Gate.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.59,0:18:24.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have two objectives.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.02,0:18:29.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First, to destroy the paper on time machines,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.32,0:18:31.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,which Professor Nakabachi took to Russia.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.71,0:18:36.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Second, to save Makise Kurisu.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.02,0:18:37.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I could do that...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.67,0:18:43.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But avoiding her death and \Nchanging the past are impossible
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.04,0:18:46.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,because of the Attractor Field convergence.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.02,0:18:47.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.22,0:18:49.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be as clear as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.19,0:18:50.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Saving Makise Kurisu is possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.77,0:18:53.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're just approaching it the wrong way.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.88,0:18:56.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen well.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.71,0:18:59.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You must not change the past, \Nonce it's been established.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.54,0:19:03.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You must not undo what you saw that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.42,0:19:08.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you do either, the past will change, \Nand all will be lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.59,0:19:13.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Remember your experiences \Nin the alpha world line.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.27,0:19:16.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was only three weeks,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.43,0:19:20.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but you should have memories \Nof your time with Makise Kurisu.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.77,0:19:25.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of all you and she sacrificed to save Mayuri.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.52,0:19:30.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of everything that happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.53,0:19:36.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You must not waste those three weeks.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.62,0:19:39.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You must not undo them.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.35,0:19:43.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The only reason you wish so desperately to save her
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.74,0:19:47.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is because of the world lines you experienced.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.77,0:19:49.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And it's the sole reason
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.78,0:19:52.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I devoted my life to developing a time machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.77,0:19:55.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The reason you've managed to get
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.85,0:19:59.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,as far as you have is that \Nwe both want to save Kurisu.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.29,0:20:03.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So you must deceive your other self.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.17,0:20:08.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Save her without changing the past where she died.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.84,0:20:10.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Make your past self
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.75,0:20:13.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,mistake a living Kurisu for a dead one.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.76,0:20:17.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you do, the past won't change.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.60,0:20:18.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I get it...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.26,0:20:20.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What does he mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.78,0:20:22.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okarin, do you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.17,0:20:23.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know you'll understand me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.15,0:20:28.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, the time machine's ID is C204.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.90,0:20:32.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you know what that stands for.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.68,0:20:34.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Christina...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.67,0:20:39.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And I was the one who named \Nthe target world line Steins Gate.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.53,0:20:44.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You know why I named it that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.39,0:20:47.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't really mean anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.52,0:20:49.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.27,0:20:54.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will now explain the parameters
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.81,0:20:57.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,of the final mission, Operation Skuld.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.10,0:21:00.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Change the result without changing \Nthe established past.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.67,0:21:04.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The past consists of Makise Kurisu, \Nlying in a bloody pool,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.34,0:21:07.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and Okabe Rintarou seeing her there.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.10,0:21:10.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Change the past without changing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.54,0:21:13.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Deceive your other self.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.68,0:21:15.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Deceive the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.12,0:21:20.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is what you must do to reach Steins Gate.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.86,0:21:24.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.80,0:21:27.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,El Psy Congroo.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.31,0:21:31.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.52,0:21:35.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Was that you, fifteen years from now?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.22,0:21:37.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The voice was so deep!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.46,0:21:47.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Operation Skuld?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.63,0:21:49.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,El Psy Congroo?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.60,0:21:53.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I still talk like that when I'm thirty-three years old?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.62,0:21:58.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I sound like an otaku who's read \Ntoo many bad light novels.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.76,0:22:00.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okarin?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.59,0:22:03.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.19,0:22:07.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If that is the choice of Steins Gate.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.29,0:22:13.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am the mad scientist, Hououin Kyouma!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.18,0:22:16.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Deceiving the world is nothing to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.05,0:22:23.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's back to the usual Okarin.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.38,0:22:27.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Mayushii likes Okarin better \Nwhen he's like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.58,0:22:30.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll say it once more.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.81,0:22:38.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am the mad scientist, Hououin Kyouma...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.97,0:22:44.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And the world is in the palm of my hand!
